surgical care affiliates  wikipedia surgical care affiliates from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search surgical care affiliates inc type public traded as nasdaq scai sp  component industry healthcare predecessor surgical care affiliates  to  healthsouth outpatient surgery division  to  founded  headquarters deerfield illinois number of locations  key people andrew hayek chairman and chief executive officer joseph t clark chief development officer tom de weerdt chief financial officer michael rucker chief operating officer rich sharff general counsel products ambulatory surgery centers and surgical hospitals revenue  billion usd   number of employees    website wwwscasurgerycom surgical care affiliates inc sca is one of the largest providers of outpatient surgery in the united states based in deerfield illinois the company has a network of more than  ambulatory surgery centers ascs located in  states performing  million procedures a year sca creates partnerships between health plans physician groups and health systems to acquire develop and optimize surgical facilities scas affiliated physicians provide a range of surgical services including orthopedics ophthalmology gastroenterology pain management otolaryngology ear nose and throat or ent urology spine cardiology and gynecology as well as other general surgery procedures sca’s partners include large surgeon groups eg orthocarolina illinois bone and joint the core institute disc jewett orthopedics large multispeciality groups eg monarch healthcare davita healthcare partners austin regional clinic and large health systems eg advocate healthcare texas health resources memorialcare health system sca is a publicly traded company and its shares are listed on the nasdaq global select market under the symbol scai on january   sca and optum part of unitedhealth group nyse unh announced the two companies would combine the agreement calls for the acquisition of sca’s outstanding common stock for  per share in this agreement sca will become part of the optumcare platform with hayek and the sca leadership team continuing forward as part of sca and the larger optumcare platform the deal is expected to close in the first half of  contents  history  sca today  partnerships  recognition  medical missions  references  external links historyedit origins surgical care affiliates was founded in  by joel gordon in nashville tennessee gordon had previously founded general care corp nyse gce in  a hospital company that was sold to hospital corporation of america “hca” in  subsequent to selling general care corp to hca gordon partnered with andrew “woody” miller an hca executive and jack massey a cofounder of hca and american venture capitalist to launch sca sca raised capital by listing shares on the new york stock exchange and used the proceeds to acquire existing surgery centers and build new surgery centers mostly in the southeast from  to  sca grew to approximately  facilities with ken melkus serving as the ceo for most of that time early growth from  to  sca grew to approximately  facilities with ken melkus serving as the ceo for most of that time healthsouth acquired sca in october  the acquisition made healthsouth the largest provider of outpatient surgery in the nation with a total of  surgery centers healthsouth acquired other surgery center companies including asc network corp and national surgery centers and independent facilities during this period in march  healthsouth announced that it would sell its surgery center division to tpg capital tpg a large private equity firm sca todayedit in june  tpg capital acquired the assets of healthsouth’s surgery division effectively forming sca as a new standalone company the company was named surgical care affiliates in recognition of the original sca current chairman and chief executive officer andrew hayek was hired in may  as president and chief executive officer hayek had previously been president of a division of davita healthcare partners and had been president and chief operating officer of alliance healthcare services sca has grown significantly since  including growing its portfolio to  facilities as of december   achieving a  compound annual growth rate cagr in ebitdanci “earnings before interest taxes depreciation and amortization less noncontrolling interests” a common industry profit metric growth from  through  generating  billion in system wide revenue in  in  sca announced its inaugural physician advisory board to provide feedback and direction on scas innovation and growth initiatives partnershipsedit texas health resources in october  sca partnered with texas health resources leadership to design and execute on a surgical strategy in the dallas  fort worth market together with community surgeons the partnership has grown from two facilities to  facilities monarch healthcare sca is partnered with monarch healthcare orange county’s largest association of physicians in private practice in  monarch healthcare was acquired by optum unitedhealth’s health services division in february  sca entered into a joint venture partnership with memorialcare medical foundation and monarch healthcare to optimize surgery in southern california the partnership now has  ascs advocate healthcare in  advocate health care and sca entered a joint venture to acquire and develop a surgery center network advocate health care was the largest fully integrated health care delivery system in the state of illinois the partnership currently has  ascs with more in development swiftpath in may  sca made an investment in swiftpath llc which develops evidencebased rapid recovery protocols that enable surgeons to perform hip and knee replacements in an outpatient setting the swiftpath platform includes patient engagement and education patient selection criteria and peerreviewed surgical techniques sca currently has  outpatient facilities performing total joint replacements recognitionedit in  sca was named one of becker’s asc review’s “best places to work in healthcare”httpwwwbeckershospitalreviewcomgreatplacestoworkinhealthcaresurgicalcareaffiliateshtml  medical missionsedit sca medical missions is a nonprofit organization that supports weeklong surgical medical mission trips to honduras for usbased physicians nurses clinical and nonclinical personnel to provide free surgical care to people who cannot afford or access care the program partnered with the holy family surgery center an ambulatory surgery center located near tegucigalpa honduras on the grounds of a  acre orphanage part of the nuestros pequeños hermanos network with more than  children referencesedit  httpwwwbeckersasccomascturnaroundsideastoimproveperformancethingstoknowaboutofbiggestasccompaniesinthemarkettodayamsurghcasurgerypartnersscauspihtml  scai  form k wwwsecgov sec   httpinvestorscasurgerycomreleasedetailcfmreleaseid  httpfilesshareholdercomdownloadsamdacklxxbccebfefacfcscaglossyannualreportbookmarkedpdfpdf  httpwwwbeckersasccomascturnaroundsideastoimproveperformancethingstoknowaboutofbiggestasccompaniesinthemarkettodayamsurghcasurgerypartnersscauspihtml  httpinvestorscasurgerycomreleasedetailcfmreleaseid  httpsfinanceyahoocomquotescailtr  httpwwwunitedhealthgroupcomnewsroomarticlesfeedoptumscaoptumcareaspx  httpwwwunitedhealthgroupcomnewsroomarticlesfeedoptumsurgicalcareaffiliatesaspxr  “surgical care affiliate” google finance httpswwwgooglecomfinanceqscaieiqhkfvhzecysaarrjwaq  httpwwwomenbookscomomenreportsomenreportstennesseespoliticalhealthcaremazehtml  httpswwwbloombergcomresearchstockssnapshotsnapshotarticleasptickersgr  httpwwwavondalepartnersllccompeoplejoelcgordon  httpnashvillepostcomnewsnashvillenowandthenendingsandbeginnings  httpwwwcompanyhistoriescomhealthsouthcorporationcompanyhistoryhtml  httpwwwsecinfocomdmxbabhtmwwwsecinfocomdmxbabhtm  httpwwwsecinfocomdmxbabhtmwwwsecinfocomdmxbabhtm  httpwwwavondalepartnersllccomaboutadvisoryboard  httpwwwavondalepartnersllccomaboutadvisoryboard 