centers and independent facilities during this period in march  healthsouth announced that it would sell its surgery center division to tpg capital tpg a large private equity firm sca todayedit in june  tpg capital acquired the assets of healthsouth’s surgery division effectively forming sca as a new standalone company the company was named surgical care affiliates in recognition of the original sca current chairman and chief executive officer andrew hayek was hired in may  as president and chief executive officer hayek had previously been president of a division of davita healthcare partners and had been president and chief operating officer of alliance healthcare services sca has grown significantly since  including growing its portfolio to  facilities as of december   achieving a  compound annual growth rate cagr in ebitdanci “earnings before interest taxes depreciation and amortization less noncontrolling interests” a common industry profit metric growth from  through  generating  billion in system wide revenue in  in  sca announced its inaugural physician advisory board to provide feedback and direction on scas innovation and growth initiatives partnershipsedit texas health resources in october  sca partnered with texas health resources leadership to design and execute on a surgical strategy in the dallas  fort worth market together with community surgeons the partnership has grown from two facilities to  facilities monarch healthcare sca is partnered with monarch healthcare orange county’s largest association of physicians in private practice in  monarch healthcare was acquired by optum unitedhealth’s health services division in february  sca entered into a joint venture partnership with memorialcare medical foundation and monarch healthcare to optimize surgery in southern california the partnership now has  ascs advocate healthcare in  advocate health care and sca entered a joint venture to acquire and develop a surgery center network advocate health care was the largest fully integrated health care delivery system in the state of illinois the partnership currently has  ascs with more in development swiftpath in may  sca made an investment in swiftpath llc which develops evidencebased rapid recovery protocols that enable surgeons to perform hip and knee replacements in an outpatient setting the swiftpath platform includes patient engagement and education patient selection criteria and peerreviewed surgical techniques sca currently has  outpatient facilities performing total joint replacements recognitionedit in  sca was named one of becker’s asc review’s “best places to work in healthcare”httpwwwbeckershospitalreviewcomgreatplacestoworkinhealthcaresurgicalcareaffiliateshtml  medical missionsedit sca medical missions is a nonprofit organization that supports weeklong surgical medical mission trips to honduras for usbased physicians nurses clinical and nonclinical personnel to provide free surgical care to people who cannot afford or access care the program partnered with the holy family surgery center an ambulatory surgery center located near tegucigalpa honduras on the grounds of a  acre orphanage part of the nuestros pequeños hermanos network with more than  children referencesedit  httpwwwbeckersasccomascturnaroundsideastoimproveperformancethingstoknowaboutofbiggestasccompaniesinthemarkettodayamsurghcasurgerypartnersscauspihtml  scai  form k wwwsecgov sec   httpinvestorscasurgerycomreleasedetailcfmreleaseid  httpfilesshareholdercomdownloadsamdacklxxbccebfefacfcscaglossyannualreportbookmarkedpdfpdf  httpwwwbeckersasccomascturnaroundsideastoimproveperformancethingstoknowaboutofbiggestasccompaniesinthemarkettodayamsurghcasurgerypartnersscauspihtml  httpinvestorscasurgerycomreleasedetailcfmreleaseid  httpsfinanceyahoocomquotescailtr  httpwwwunitedhealthgroupcomnewsroomarticlesfeedoptumscaoptumcareaspx  httpwwwunitedhealthgroupcomnewsroomarticlesfeedoptumsurgicalcareaffiliatesaspxr  “surgical care affiliate” google finance