ine the agreement calls for the acquisition of sca’s outstanding common stock for  per share in this agreement sca will become part of the optumcare platform with hayek and the sca leadership team continuing forward as part of sca and the larger optumcare platform the deal is expected to close in the first half of  contents  history  sca today  partnerships  recognition  medical missions  references  external links historyedit origins surgical care affiliates was founded in  by joel gordon in nashville tennessee gordon had previously founded general care corp nyse gce in  a hospital company that was sold to hospital corporation of america “hca” in  subsequent to selling general care corp to hca gordon partnered with andrew “woody” miller an hca executive and jack massey a cofounder of hca and american venture capitalist to launch sca sca raised capital by listing shares on the new york stock exchange and used the proceeds to acquire existing surgery centers and build new surgery centers mostly in the southeast from  to  sca grew to approximately  facilities with ken melkus serving as the ceo for most of that time early growth from  to  sca grew to approximately  facilities with ken melkus serving as the ceo for most of that time healthsouth acquired sca in october  the acquisition made healthsouth the largest provider of outpatient surgery in the nation with a total of  surgery centers healthsouth acquired other surgery center companies including asc network corp and national surgery centers and independent facilities during this period in march  healthsouth announced that it would sell its surgery center division to tpg capital tpg a large private equity firm sca todayedit in june  tpg capital acquired the assets of healthsouth’s surgery division effectively forming sca as a new standalone company the company was named surgical care affiliates in recognition of the original sca current chairman and chief executive officer andrew hayek was hired in may  as president